        "text": "This was yummy but... I'm not a fan of one pot meals. I'm giving this 3 stars because all of the flavor elements are there. Let's face it, most pasta comes in a 12 oz package and a can of diced tomatoes are 14.5 oz. People making one pot meals don't usually have kitchen scales. I made this with 1 lb. of turkey kielbasa, a 12 oz box of dried farfalle (bowties), a can of petite diced tomatoes and doubled all of the liquids. Please learn from my experience. This recipe is totally going in my repertoire as I have explained it. Enjoy!"

Sweet caramelized onions, pan-browned kielbasa sausage, and a sprinkle of fresh herbs make this quick, cozy dish pop on the plate. For the best results, you'll need a 12-inch nonstick frying pan. If you don't have a nonstick pan this big, you can use a regular frying pan, but you'll need more oil, you'll have to handle the pierogi carefully, and they may break apart a bit.                     "description": "Pierogi are classic Polish dumplings, made by wrapping dough around a savory filling and then boiling. This quick and easy, semi-homemade meal takes advantage of store-bought frozen pierogi for a no-boil, one-pot dish that comes together in about 40 minutes. Sweet caramelized onions, pan-browned kielbasa sausage, and a sprinkle of fresh herbs make this quick, cozy dish pop on the plate. For the best results, you'll need a 12-inch nonstick frying pan. If you don't have a nonstick pan this big, you can use a regular frying pan, but you'll need more oil, you'll have to handle the pierogi carefully, and they may break apart a bit. The recipe is a Yummly original created by [Tory L. Davis](https://www.yummly.com/dish/author/Tory-L-Davis).",

                  "name": "Weeknight Pan-Fried Pierogi and Kielbasa Recipe | Yummly",
                  "description": "Pierogi are classic Polish dumplings, made by wrapping dough around a savory filling and then boiling. This quick and easy, semi-homemade meal takes advantage of store-bought frozen pierogi for a no-boil, one-pot dish that comes together in about 40 minutes. Sweet caramelized onions, pan-browned kielbasa sausage, and a sprinkle of fresh herbs make this quick, cozy dish pop on the plate. For the best results, you'll need a 12-inch nonstick frying pan. If you don't have a nonstick pan this big, you can use a regular frying pan, but you'll need more oil, you'll have to handle the pierogi carefully, and they may break apart a bit. The recipe is a Yummly original created by [Tory L. Davis](https://www.yummly.com/dish/author/Tory-L-Davis)."

Turn the lobster tails over so the hard shells are on top, still with the tails pointed away from you. Using kitchen shears or other sturdy scissors, cut lengthwise through the center of each shell, starting at the body end (bottom) and stopping just before the tail fins (top).             "name": "Weeknight Pan-Fried Pierogi and Kielbasa",
            "description": "Pierogi are classic Polish dumplings, made by wrapping dough around a savory filling and then boiling. This quick and easy, semi-homemade meal takes advantage of store-bought frozen pierogi for a no-boil, one-pot dish that comes together in about 40 minutes. Sweet caramelized onions, pan-browned kielbasa sausage, and a sprinkle of fresh herbs make this quick, cozy dish pop on the plate. For the best results, you'll need a 12-inch nonstick frying pan. If you don't have a nonstick pan this big, you can use a regular frying pan, but you'll need more oil, you'll have to handle the pierogi carefully, and they may break apart a bit. The recipe is a Yummly original created by [Tory L. Davis](https://www.yummly.com/dish/author/Tory-L-Davis).",

This quick and easy, semi-homemade meal takes advantage of store-bought frozen pierogi for a no-boil, one-pot dish that comes together in about 40 minutes.
